    "longDescription": "The HTU Design Expo Voting Platform was designed and developed from the ground up as a production-grade web application to manage the audience-voting experience at HTU's annual Design Expo. The platform handled real-time project discovery, authenticated fan voting, live result tracking, kiosk-mode display, and a permanent Hall of Fame archive — all within a single cohesive system.\n\nOutcomes:\n\n• 🗳️ Successfully processed hundreds of real-time votes across all expo attendees with zero data conflicts or duplicate votes\n\n• 📱 Achieved 100% mobile compatibility — fully responsive across all screen sizes from 320px up to 4K displays\n\n• 🔒 Zero security breaches — Firestore Security Rules enforced atomic transactions and prevented vote manipulation at the database level\n\n• 🌐 Delivered a seamless bilingual experience in both English and Arabic with proper RTL layout support\n\n• 🏆 Produced a permanent Hall of Fame archive preserving the top 6 judging winners and the Fan Favorite Award winner with verified final vote counts\n\n• ⚡ Sub-second real-time sync across all devices — vote counts and status changes propagated instantly via Firestore listeners\n\n• 🖥️ Powered a live kiosk display running autonomously throughout the expo with zero manual intervention\n\n• 🚀 Deployed and live on GitHub Pages with an automated CI build pipeline",
