    "description": "The ANS project presents an innovative solution to support individuals with paralysis by developing a system that utilizes artificial intelligence (AI) to restore motor functions. The system works by capturing brain signals, analyzing them, and transmitting them to a device that can move the affected body part.",
    "longDescription": "AI plays a crucial role in this project through:\n\t1.\tNeural Signal Analysis: Using machine learning to identify patterns in brain signals related to movement.\n\t2.\tSignal Translation: Converting brain signals into clear, actionable commands for the movement device.\n\t3.\tPersonalized Adaptation: Learning and adapting to the unique brain signals of each patient over time.\n\t4.\tAutomatic Error Correction: Detecting and correcting inaccurate signals for smoother movements.\n\t5.\tReal-Time Interaction: Ensuring quick and accurate responses to brain signals for natural motion.",
